":24,"text":"The gates were toward the four winds, eastward, westward, northward, southward.","searchKeywords":["the","gates","were","toward","four","winds","eastward","westward","northward","southward"]},{"verseId":"brenton_1-chronicles_9_25","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":13,"bookName":"1 Chronicles","bookAbbrev":"1-chronicles","chapter":9,"verse":25,"text":"And their brethren in their courts, to enter in weekly from time to time with these.","searchKeywords":["and","their","brethren","courts","enter","weekly","from","time","with","these"]},{"verseId":"brenton_1-chronicles_9_26","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":13,"bookName":"1 Chronicles","bookAbbrev":"1-chronicles","chapter":9,"verse":26,"text":"For four strong have the charge of the gates; and the Levites were over the chambers, and they keep watch over the treasures of the house of God.","searchKeywords":["for","four","strong","have","the","charge","gates","and","levites","were","over","chambers","they","keep","watch","treasures","house","god"]},{"verseId":"brenton_1-chronicles_9_27","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":13,"bookName":"1 Chronicles","bookAbbrev":"1-chronicles","chapter":9,"verse":27,"text":"For the charge upon them, and these charged with the keys to open the doors of the temple every morning.","searchKeywords":["for","the","charge","upon","them","and","these","charged","with","keys","open","doors","temple","every","morning"]},{"verseId":"brenton_1-chronicles_9_28","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":13,"bookName":"1 Chronicles","bookAbbrev":"1-chronicles","chapter":9,"verse":28,"text":"And of them over the vessels of service, that they should carry them in by number, and carry them out by number.","searchKeywords":["and","them","over","the","vessels","service","that","they","should","carry","number","out"]},{"verseId":"brenton_1-chronicles_9_29","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":13,"bookName":"1 Chronicles","bookAbbrev":"1-chronicles","chapter":9,"verse":29,"text":"And of them appointed over the furniture, and over all the holy vessels, and over the fine flour, the wine, the oil, the frankincense, and the spices.","searchKeywords":["and","them","appointed","over","the","furniture","all","holy","vessels","fine","flour","wine","oil","frankincense","spices"]},{"verseId":"brenton_1-chronicles_9_30","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":13,"bookName":"1 Chronicles","bookAbbrev":"1-chronicles","chapter":9,"verse":30,"text":"And some of the priests were makers of the ointment, and the spices.","searchKeywords":["and","some","the","priests","were","makers","ointment","spices"]},{"verseId":"brenton_1-chronicles_9_31","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":13,"bookName":"1 Chronicles","bookAbbrev":"1-chronicles","chapter":9,"verse":31,"text":"And Matthathias of the Levites, (he the first-born of Salom the Corite,) in charge over the sacrifices of meat-offering of the pan belonging to the high priest.","searchKeywords":["and","matthathias","the","levites","first","born","salom","corite","charge","over","sacrifices","meat","offering","pan","belonging","high","priest"]},{"verseId":"brenton_1-chronicles_9_32","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":13,"bookName":"1 Chronicles","bookAbbrev":"1-chronicles","chapter":9,"verse":32,"text":"And Banaias the Caathite, from among their brethren, over the shewbread, to prepare it every sabbath.","searchKeywords":["and","banaias","the","caathite","from","among","their","brethren","over","shewbread","prepare","every","sabbath"]},{"verseId":"brenton_1-chronicles_9_33","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":13,"bookName":"1 Chronicles","bookAbbrev":"1-chronicles","chapter":9,"verse":33,"text":"And these the singers, heads of families of the Levites, established daily courses, for they were employed in the services day and night.","searchKeywords":["and","these","the"